Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.01,0:00:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for 35 years, psychoanalyst, physician, researcher
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the relationship between nutrition and the relationship to alcoholism and addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for the last 10 years doing research into the nature of consciousness itself and its
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship to that which is called spiritual. And today's talk is going to be on understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.22,0:00:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of addiction, letting go of alcoholism and addiction. And we'll be presenting this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.36,0:00:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,whole topic of alcoholism and addiction from the viewpoint of consciousness itself, a different
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.82,0:00:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,way of approaching the topic, a way of discerning what is the essential nature of the addictive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.40,0:00:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,process rather than what are its consequences or its physical correlates. We'll be talking
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.86,0:00:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,about the nature of consciousness itself and how...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.14,0:00:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.22,0:01:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So understanding of this will give us a different context in which to understand the addictive
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.44,0:01:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,process and its relationship to human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.40,0:01:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll be looking today at a map of consciousness, one that we've used in this series of talks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.40,0:01:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and one which we have found has been very useful in research and making understandable
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.52,0:01:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that which hitherto for has been perhaps considered mystical.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.14,0:01:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been considered mystical, or esoteric, or too right-brained for a left-brained people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.36,0:01:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And so on the blackboard here we have what looks complicated but actually is quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.47,0:01:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The various levels of consciousness and these levels as you can see have been calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.03,0:01:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of the research we've done, for instance, we have calibrated the relative power of these
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.39,0:01:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,energy fields and their direction. And we will begin to understand a lot of human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.69,0:02:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of that we'll understand the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In this calibration you'll notice where death is calibrated at zero, if death is calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.79,0:02:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,at zero, then we will find an enlightenment, or leaving the world of duality, transcending
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.63,0:02:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,limitation calibrates at about 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.11,0:02:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We notice that the energy field of courage is at 200, pride 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.43,0:02:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll refer back to these numbers in the course of our discussion. Importantly also we'll notice that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.61,0:02:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the direction of these arrows shows whether it is a negative energy field, that which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.61,0:02:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is not inimicable to life, or whether it's a positive energy field, that which is supportive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.23,0:02:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In understanding addiction then, we need to understand the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,first, and then we'll go back to how this applies to the addictive process. We'll look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.72,0:02:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at what is the true nature of addiction, and what is the quality that society has missed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:02:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because society's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.03,0:03:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of addiction has not been very successful. Until the advent of Alcoholics
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.37,0:03:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Anonymous, let us say, society's recovery rate from the addictions was zero. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.91,0:03:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,never heard of that anybody ever recovered from alcoholism, and it was only the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.39,0:03:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as represented by Carl Jung, who said that science alone has no answer for this problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.13,0:03:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.21,0:03:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,over-ambiguously
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.93,0:03:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond ordinary human experience, meaning within the limitations of science, has to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.85,0:03:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,be sought, and there the answer will be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.11,0:03:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And that brings in then spirituality, and what does that mean? We'll be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.71,0:03:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the relationship between body, mind, and spirit. What is the relationship between body, mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.76,0:03:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and spirit? And what is spirit anyway? Is it some kind of a mythical entity? Is it a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.62,0:04:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,metaphysical fantasy? What is the nature of spirit, and how does it operate in a real
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.87,0:04:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,way that we can verify through our own clinical experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.15,0:04:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we won't be talking about philosophy. We won't be talking about epistemology. We're
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.61,0:04:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be talking about that which you can verify for yourself through your own inner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,experience, and truth as it can be experienced within yourself, and then how this is going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.41,0:04:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to be applied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.13,0:04:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So today we'll be talking about the understanding of alcoholism and the addictions, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.23,0:04:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,importance thereof in their recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.67,0:04:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so today we'll be talking about context. The overall way in which you hold a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the space from which you're coming, how to be with a subject, because it's context
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that creates all of meaning. It's context that defines goal, and coming from a context
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,of understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.09,0:04:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.29,0:05:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll go to this map today, and we'll start explaining it. Within the box here is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.57,0:05:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, the ego, that which is called the self with a small s. And within the ego we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.79,0:05:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,see we have these different energy fields which we mentioned before. Starting at the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.59,0:05:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom, then, we have an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy field is called guilt. And you'll notice over to the right of these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is an emotion, an emotion, how we experience this energy field in our daily life. And to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.17,0:05:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the right of that we'll notice a process, the process which is going on within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.07,0:05:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy field will also determine how we experience and see the world, how we see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the world, and how we would relate to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of our understanding, because of the limitation of our own energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.31,0:06:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And starting at the bottom, as we said, is an energy field called guilt. And we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,it is calibrated with 30, using death as zero, 30 then, is a state of, really a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.95,0:06:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction. And it's experienced usually in the form of self-hatred. And the world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.35,0:06:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is seen as a place of sin and suffering. And God is really the ultimate, the ultimate, the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.65,0:06:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,threat or destroyer of the soul, because he will throw the soul into destruction, into
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,hellfire forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.92,0:06:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is really the lowest energy field, and one with very little power in it. And
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.97,0:06:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,when we move up to the next one, we move up to an energy field of hopelessness and despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.75,0:06:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,which is calibrated at 50.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.77,0:06:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness and despair means, for instance, like the old lady rocking back and forth in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.31,0:06:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,her rocking chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She's staring out the window, and she got a notice from the State Department that her
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.63,0:07:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,son was killed in action.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.43,0:07:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, the family shakes her, you know, and tries to get her to respond, and she doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.65,0:07:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,respond to anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Because accompanying these energy fields, there's changes in brain chemistry. There's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.97,0:07:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,been a happening now within her neurotransmitters, within her brain, and so that she doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.23,0:07:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So hopelessness and despair represents a process going on within her brain, and so that she
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.23,0:07:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So hopelessness and despair represents a process going on within her brain, and so that she
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.79,0:07:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So hopelessness and despair represents a process going on in consciousness of loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.54,0:07:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is seen as hopeless, and if there is a God, he would have nothing to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.06,0:07:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you, because your own self-esteem is so low that God wouldn't want anything to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.58,0:07:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a worm like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.88,0:07:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So we call it sort of the worm view of the nature of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.57,0:07:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If we get the person out of that very low energy field, we can get them up to a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.89,0:08:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field called grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in hopelessness cannot help themself, and we have to pour energy into them, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.89,0:08:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,if we can, we can get them up perhaps to this energy field called grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.37,0:08:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief calibrates at 75.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.13,0:08:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a lot more energy than hopelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.33,0:08:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief has a certain biologic purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the child, when it cries, summons the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.79,0:08:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.25,0:08:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.25,0:08:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It has the power to pull some kind of response from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And the emotion that accompanies grief is one of regret, a feeling of loss, a feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.47,0:08:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of despondency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.21,0:08:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the process going on in consciousness is dispirited, spirit being that high energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all of life is a manifestation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.66,0:08:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in grief then sees this as a very sad world and an unloving God who doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.24,0:08:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,really care for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.28,0:09:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is a very sad world and an unloving God who doesn't really care for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.37,0:09:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if we have the old lady rocking back and forth in her rocking chair and not eating
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and not responding, and let's say we get a telegram from the State Department that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,says the previous telegram was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.73,0:09:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really someone else with a different name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And the family gathers around to her and they say, mother, mother, it wasn't Joey that got
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.49,0:09:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.49,0:09:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive and well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.49,0:09:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And she goes right on rocking back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.37,0:09:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.37,0:09:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.55,0:09:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.59,0:09:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Still standing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.73,0:09:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.79,0:09:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.03,0:09:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.05,0:09:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.09,0:09:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.21,0:09:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,staring out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If we could get that woman now by pouring energy into her up to a level of grief, all
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.44,0:09:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of a sudden she begins to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.60,0:09:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression of that emotion now indicates to us that she is getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.49,0:09:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly enough, these two energy states come out of the failure to face the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.19,0:09:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,field which lies just above it called fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.58,0:10:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field of fear, still a negative emotion as you can see by the direction of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.64,0:10:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the arrow, but an energy field now of 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.14,0:10:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,100 is a lot of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.60,0:10:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you can run a long way out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.88,0:10:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the emotion itself, the form of the emotion is not constructive, but the energy out of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.26,0:10:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be utilized in a very positive way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.48,0:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so all these energy fields have their upside and their downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.76,0:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside which can be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.68,0:10:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Negatively, the upside, if you know how to utilize it, you can utilize the energy of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.60,0:10:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.60,0:10:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you know what to be afraid of, it can be a very constructive thing in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.72,0:10:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear as we ordinarily experience it in ordinary life is experienced as worry, anxiety, panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.26,0:10:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually even terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.76,0:10:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So grief, you see, has to do with the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.14,0:10:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief has to do with the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And fear has to do with the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.14,0:10:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The process going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.54,0:11:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is one of deflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.64,0:11:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The fearful animal shrinks and hides.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in third grade and the teacher asks for a response to a question, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how we used to shrink and hide behind the person in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we shrink and become deflated less than that which we are in fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the kind of world that we see, our perception of the world that comes out of this energy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.06,0:11:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,field is that this is a frightening and threatening world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.74,0:11:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See how we can take away from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And who is the god of a frightening and threatening world?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.02,0:11:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A very punitive god.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, god is seen as a punisher, and much to be feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.12,0:11:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the holding of all the sense of sin and guilt, and low self-esteem in this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,level of consciousness, holds god as the most frightening of all possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.00,0:11:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving a person out of fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.30,0:12:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're able to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.30,0:12:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the next energy field, which we call desire, and desire at 125, as you know, has
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.18,0:12:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,an awful lot of energy, desiring to want.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So its expression in our ordinary emotion is that of wanting and craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.44,0:12:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That can eventually become an obsession, a compulsion, and we then call it an addiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.98,0:12:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is this so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.92,0:12:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the process going on in consciousness is one of entrapment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.40,0:12:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has become entrapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.06,0:12:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They are at the effect of, they are run by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.82,0:12:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the marketing industry, of course, this is their purpose, to create in you, to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.64,0:12:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,play off your desires, to create a wanting and a craving, to get you entrapped to want
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.16,0:12:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.06,0:12:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you become entrapped by that, whether it's a fancy car or a certain perfume or a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:12:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,shampoo that's going to make you lovely, whatever, then that will run you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'd be willing to give up your money and your energy and buy their product.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.00,0:13:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Desiringness, however, leads to a world because of the endless wantingness of this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.66,0:13:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of your solar plexus of a very frustrating world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.94,0:13:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with wantingness is though it can drive you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting a Ph.D., the wanting to be a doctor, the wanting to live in a good address.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.34,0:13:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All these wantings, which can run us for an entire lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.70,0:13:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,lead to a certain sense of frustration because wantingness does not cure itself by getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.94,0:13:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It just leads to additional wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, after you finally get a yacht, you will find that as you tie it up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody next to you has a bigger yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.19,0:13:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the wantingness in and of itself is not satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this constant frustration leads to a picture of God from whom you're separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.25,0:13:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, He's the God who forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.61,0:14:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who never withholds from you what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.65,0:14:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it leads easily to anger, which is our next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anger, at 150, as everyone is aware, of course, leads to, has a great deal of energy in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.72,0:14:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,As you see, it's still a negative emotion and it has a destructive downside.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But the energy of anger, if you know how to use it, it can be a very useful thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We experience the energy of anger, you know, in every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, in the emotions of resentment, of feeling hatred, grievances, grudges,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.98,0:14:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the unwillingness to forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.30,0:14:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that what's happened in the process in consciousness is one of expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.74,0:14:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The angry animal swells up with anger, becomes larger than life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.18,0:14:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who's angry, their veins swell, they swell up with this angriness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.52,0:14:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to become imposing on the biologic level, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This angriness, then, leads to a competitiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The angry person sees a world of competition, of conflict, of war, of me against you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a polarized position of opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, the God, understand, the view of God that comes out of that is an angry God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.85,0:15:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person who sees God is the ultimate,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.51,0:15:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.19,0:15:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of angriness, the God of vengeance, the God who gets even.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.73,0:15:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the God who's coming out of his spleen, is he not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.33,0:15:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming out of a revenge, a hatred, an anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.89,0:15:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though he now hates that which he created
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.43,0:15:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and hates the humanness of that which he created.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.80,0:15:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of retaliatory, vengeful angriness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.98,0:16:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If we move up out of this angriness, if we can move up to pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.92,0:16:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that pride has an energy field of 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.92,0:16:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a lot of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.92,0:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And pride is enough to energize the United States Marine Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride can be a very useful emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with pride, because we see the energy field of it is still in a negative direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotions experienced with pride, the downside of it is denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the addictions, of course, this is very, can be very fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.87,0:16:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Denial, taking the form of arrogance and contempt, saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.87,0:16:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's good, you know, those people need it, but not me, I'm different.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.87,0:16:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And that comes out of the fact that the process going on in consciousness is one of inflated.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is coming from an inflated sense of self, a very dangerous position,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.87,0:16:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we see the pridefulness which leads to the destruction eventually,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.87,0:17:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the rapid destruction, coming down to destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.87,0:17:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the rock stars and people who get into drugs who are successful very early in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.87,0:17:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,this enormous inflation of the ego, the denial that goes with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.87,0:17:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the contempt for the valuation of life, the inability to hear the advice of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.96,0:17:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness leads us to then a very vulnerable defensiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a good position to be in,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.96,0:17:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's an energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.96,0:17:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an energy that we can utilize when we're moving ourselves from anger up to courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, out of this energy field of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.51,0:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in pride then is very preoccupied with status, with ownership,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,with havingness, with symbols, with labels.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.21,0:17:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a very defensive position to be in, this preoccupation with status.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.50,0:18:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that energy field, which comes out as denial, arrogance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.50,0:18:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,contempt, an inflated energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.66,0:18:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,how does that influence our viewpoint of God?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.85,0:18:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship to God then would be one of usually two possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.85,0:18:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the arrogance of the intellect, out of the left brainness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.85,0:18:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the presumption that the left brain has the capacity to know all of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.08,0:18:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,could come a position of atheism.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the position of atheism then is a denial,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.81,0:18:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a denial of the truth of which can be experienced through human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.16,0:18:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it could take its opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.16,0:18:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It could take the form of bigotry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.16,0:18:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It could take the form of the religionist,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.16,0:18:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who takes the position then that my way of seeing things is the only way,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and because my way is the truth, your way, therefore, is not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.16,0:18:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So pride is a position which polarizes us,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.16,0:19:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in which everybody else then becomes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,see there's our position, which is correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore everybody else's position is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.16,0:19:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So pridefulness then is a polarizing position of me against you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.16,0:19:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it is the basis of all the religious wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride has a useful energy in it, as the Marine Corps has found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.06,0:19:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's useful to us to move on through to a higher energy field called courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.06,0:19:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now courage is a very crucial level to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.06,0:19:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And crucial because you see, for one thing, the arrow now suddenly goes neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.06,0:19:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, the energy field of that level of consciousness is now shifted to neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.06,0:19:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though the negative antenna, the antenna which was tuned to negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.06,0:19:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is now tuned to neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.06,0:19:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It stops pulling to itself in experience that which is negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.06,0:20:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Its energy field is 200, which is a lot of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.06,0:20:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So courage has enough energy in it, you know, to settle the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Courage has enough to get a man to the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It has enough to establish all of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.48,0:20:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to explore intellectual frontiers of philosophy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.48,0:20:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So courage at 200 is enough to create all the great industrial empires.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.51,0:20:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a very powerful energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.51,0:20:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,not because it jumped another 25 points,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.08,0:20:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but because now the direction of the field has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of that resistance has dropped off.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.08,0:20:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the first time now, the person emotionally is able to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.08,0:20:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to cope, to handle, to look at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.08,0:20:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And the critical thing that happens in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.08,0:20:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the process going on in consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the person becomes empowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.08,0:20:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The person becomes empowered.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.08,0:20:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And what made this huge jump?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What made this huge jump in power?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.08,0:21:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What crosses the line and makes you go beyond that level
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.08,0:21:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.47,0:21:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be crucial in the understanding of the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.47,0:21:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the understanding of the traditional 12 steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.47,0:21:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is in the first step,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the admission that one is powerless over alcohol and drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.47,0:21:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is making our life unbearable,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that changes this entire energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.47,0:21:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and re-empowers the person now
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.47,0:21:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and puts them in a position of recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.33,0:21:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of view of the world takes place
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.33,0:21:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from this energy field of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.33,0:21:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when you start telling the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.33,0:21:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to see this as a world of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.33,0:21:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it as a world of challenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,a very exciting world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.33,0:21:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in which to grow and experience one's growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.33,0:21:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of a view of God comes about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.33,0:21:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,These were all below the line of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.33,0:22:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we tested them all with kinesiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.33,0:22:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we find that you go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.33,0:22:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are denials of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.33,0:22:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of this energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of view of God opens up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.33,0:22:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is the open mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.33,0:22:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, the person really tells the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.33,0:22:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is that through one's own experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.33,0:22:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,one has not really had an experience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.33,0:22:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of what there is called God within the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.33,0:22:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, through that question mark then,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.33,0:22:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for the first time, the mind is open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.33,0:22:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The person begins to ask the traditional questions
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.33,0:22:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which have always led to the ultimate realization
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.33,0:22:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth of that question.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a God? Is He experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.33,0:22:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it be experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.33,0:22:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it something I can verify within myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.75,0:22:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is God something out there or within me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.75,0:22:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it express itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.75,0:22:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I get to know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.75,0:22:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole spiritual exploration begins then
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.75,0:22:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,with the beginning of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.75,0:22:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.75,0:23:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,of the first level of integrity, of empowerment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.75,0:23:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.75,0:23:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which gives us the power,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.75,0:23:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us the power to face and cope and handle
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.75,0:23:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the first time be appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.75,0:23:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the energy field of courage then,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.55,0:23:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to look at the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.55,0:23:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and admit the truth about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.55,0:23:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we can move to the next energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.55,0:23:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is called neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.55,0:23:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here you see the arrow now
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.55,0:23:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is positively going to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field has jumped to two levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.55,0:23:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.64,0:23:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And how is that level experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.64,0:23:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's experienced as being unattached.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.64,0:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you've told the truth about a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.64,0:23:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you may move up to a process
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.68,0:23:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we call released,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.68,0:23:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you're no longer attached to outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.71,0:23:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what is a person like
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.71,0:23:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,on this energy field of neutral?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.71,0:23:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're in a state, we would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.71,0:23:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay either way it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.71,0:23:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person on this energy level then would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.71,0:24:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,well, if I get the job, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.71,0:24:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I don't get the job, that's okay too
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.71,0:24:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'll just find another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.71,0:24:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if this relationship doesn't work out,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.71,0:24:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,well, then I'll find another relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.84,0:24:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And so there's the experience then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.84,0:24:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of the okayness of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.84,0:24:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and a sense of God as being
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.84,0:24:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of freedom,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.84,0:24:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the freedom to grow and expand
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.84,0:24:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and become conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.84,0:24:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and to begin to look into oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.84,0:24:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and the nature of human experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.84,0:24:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A God who looks favorably then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.84,0:24:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,on the exploration of your own consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.35,0:24:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So neutral is unattached.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.35,0:24:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of neutral would be sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.35,0:24:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,flat and indifferent, flat and indifferent.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.35,0:24:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside of it, we could move in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.35,0:24:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to a state called willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.35,0:24:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness, which calibrates out at about 310,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.35,0:24:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,then has a lot more power and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.35,0:24:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because for the first time intention comes in
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.35,0:24:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have said yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We say yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.35,0:25:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A person on the neutral level is sort of like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.35,0:25:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no enthusiasm there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.35,0:25:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to go to the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.35,0:25:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, we'll go to the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.35,0:25:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to go to the movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.35,0:25:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, we'll stay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.35,0:25:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not much positive there yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.35,0:25:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We've let go of the negative
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.35,0:25:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and by letting go of the negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.35,0:25:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we've created a space for willingness to come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.35,0:25:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So when willingness come in, on the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.35,0:25:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,now we have the beginning of enthusiasm,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.35,0:25:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of a positive energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.35,0:25:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We say yes, we're agreeable, we're willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.35,0:25:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So this willingness now takes us out of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.83,0:25:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,indifference, flatness and detachment
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.83,0:25:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin to experience this as a friendly world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.83,0:25:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole question of God and of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.83,0:25:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes promising and hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.83,0:25:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're now saying yes to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.83,0:25:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,See, this person is detached from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.83,0:25:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This person is willing to face
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.83,0:25:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.83,0:25:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These people don't experience what life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.83,0:26:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They're only experiencing attitudes and belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.83,0:26:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which are resisting and negative to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.83,0:26:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the energy field of the arrow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.83,0:26:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is really opposed to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.83,0:26:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,opposed to the truth of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.53,0:26:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So willingness then brings us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.53,0:26:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the next step out of willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.53,0:26:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is to move up to acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.53,0:26:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance calibrates at 380
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.53,0:26:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a person there is adequate
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.53,0:26:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and confident, capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.53,0:26:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the beginning of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.53,0:26:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the transformation of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.53,0:26:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's bringing about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.53,0:26:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,this transformation of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.53,0:26:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the person is beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.53,0:26:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to reown their own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.53,0:26:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All these fields from courage on down
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.01,0:26:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are all conditions of victim
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.01,0:26:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the person has sold out
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.01,0:26:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of their power
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.01,0:26:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and given it away to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.01,0:26:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be extremely important
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.01,0:26:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as we look at the addictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.01,0:26:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The giving away of one's power
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.01,0:26:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to that which is outside
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.01,0:26:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of oneself which brings about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.01,0:27:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.30,0:27:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is moving into acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.30,0:27:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,now is reowning that I am the source
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.30,0:27:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of happiness in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.30,0:27:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These people all think that happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.30,0:27:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,lies outside of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.30,0:27:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.30,0:27:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about through getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.30,0:27:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all conditions of lack
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.30,0:27:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in which if I get that car,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.30,0:27:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that title,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.30,0:27:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that job,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.30,0:27:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.30,0:27:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.30,0:27:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that money,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.36,0:27:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.36,0:27:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.36,0:27:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course in the addictions,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.36,0:27:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get that drug
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.36,0:27:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or if I get the right dose of that drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.36,0:27:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought that the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.36,0:27:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.36,0:27:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is what accompanies all these states
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.36,0:27:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of weakness and victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.36,0:27:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The person on the level of acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.36,0:27:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has through the willingness now,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.36,0:27:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the letting go of the resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.36,0:27:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to begin to accept
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.36,0:27:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.36,0:27:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.36,0:27:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where you put me,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.36,0:27:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I will recreate something
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.36,0:28:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that satisfies me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.36,0:28:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that person is not coming
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.36,0:28:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from powerlessness or victimhood now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.36,0:28:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That person knows that if you put them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.74,0:28:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,on a desert island someplace
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.74,0:28:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come back a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.74,0:28:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you'll have
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.74,0:28:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a coconut factory going,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.74,0:28:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll have a tree house
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.74,0:28:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,built in the tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.74,0:28:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be teaching French
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.74,0:28:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to the natives,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.74,0:28:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find a native girl
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.74,0:28:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,who started a new family all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.74,0:28:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That power then to recreate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.16,0:28:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.16,0:28:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who is putting
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.44,0:28:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you in prison let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.44,0:28:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what's happening in prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At one hand you have suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.44,0:28:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.44,0:28:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you have people who have written
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.44,0:28:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,great prize winning novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.44,0:28:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have changed the course
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.44,0:28:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of all human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.44,0:28:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have written these incredible
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.44,0:28:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and powerful and brilliant books
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,while in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.44,0:28:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.44,0:28:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see the power is not in the prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.44,0:28:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the power is in the self.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.44,0:28:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the capacity then to use
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.44,0:28:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,even the prison experience
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.44,0:28:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in a valuable and positive way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.44,0:28:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to create a great novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.44,0:28:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a great book,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.44,0:29:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a political treatise.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.24,0:29:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of the greatest things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.24,0:29:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ever written were written
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.24,0:29:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,under conditions that the person
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.24,0:29:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,down here would see as impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.24,0:29:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance that you are the source
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.24,0:29:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,then makes this seem like
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.24,0:29:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a harmonious world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.24,0:29:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That you are the source
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.24,0:29:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of happiness within your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.24,0:29:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And the view of God
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.24,0:29:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.24,0:29:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,promising hopeful view
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.24,0:29:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is of course the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.24,0:29:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of the merciful God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.28,0:29:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of mercy,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.28,0:29:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.28,0:29:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,as you move up into
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.28,0:29:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.28,0:29:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.47,0:29:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the owning of the power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.47,0:29:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.47,0:29:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,moving more towards truth
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.47,0:29:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness now
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.47,0:29:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to become truly loving
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.47,0:29:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and we move up to now
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.47,0:29:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a powerful energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.47,0:29:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a plus 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.47,0:29:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of love itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.69,0:29:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where happiness begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.69,0:29:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness when you calibrate it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.69,0:29:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,begins at an energy field of 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.69,0:29:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.69,0:29:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,more and more of gettingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.69,0:29:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is down in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.69,0:30:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,getting money, sex, power,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.69,0:30:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,positions, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.69,0:30:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,does not bring happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.69,0:30:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It brings pleasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.69,0:30:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,brings momentary fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.69,0:30:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.69,0:30:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if 50 million won't make you happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.69,0:30:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,why 75 won't either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.69,0:30:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because more millions
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.69,0:30:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is only a 200 energy field experience
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.69,0:30:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and happiness begins at 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.24,0:30:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning then
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.24,0:30:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field of love
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.24,0:30:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and what kind of love
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.24,0:30:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are we talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.24,0:30:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.24,0:30:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.24,0:30:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We are talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.24,0:30:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a stable energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.24,0:30:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which nurtures,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.24,0:30:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which supports,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.24,0:30:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which comes forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.24,0:30:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of it also becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.24,0:30:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.24,0:30:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation into the truth of life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.24,0:30:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is due to the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.24,0:30:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that within the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,at an energy field of 500
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.24,0:30:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially at 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.24,0:30:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there is the release of endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:30:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning real alteration,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.24,0:30:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the correlation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.24,0:30:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on the physical level
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.24,0:30:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,within the brain chemistry itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.24,0:30:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The view of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.30,0:31:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of this lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.30,0:31:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of course is a loving world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.30,0:31:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and a God of unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.30,0:31:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and unconditional forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.30,0:31:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very important point
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.04,0:31:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for us who are in the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.04,0:31:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.04,0:31:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.04,0:31:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of Alcoholics Anonymous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.04,0:31:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcotics Anonymous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.04,0:31:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Overeaters Anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.04,0:31:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.04,0:31:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which are based on spiritual principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.04,0:31:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate out at an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.04,0:31:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.04,0:31:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is a critical level
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.23,0:31:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.23,0:31:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the level of healing
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.23,0:31:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.23,0:31:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,An energy field of 540
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.23,0:31:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of the nature of that field
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.23,0:31:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is a healing field,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.23,0:31:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,one which is unconditionally loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.32,0:31:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This represents then
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.32,0:31:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a commitment, an alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.32,0:31:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This forgivingness becomes automatic
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.03,0:31:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because out of the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.03,0:31:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the kind of a world
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.03,0:32:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which is revealed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.03,0:32:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What's revealed to you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.03,0:32:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is that what is important
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.03,0:32:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.03,0:32:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of that understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.03,0:32:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually move up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.03,0:32:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to levels of compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.03,0:32:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.03,0:32:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.03,0:32:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that becomes foremost in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.03,0:32:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,is revealed as what is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.03,0:32:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has a fractured hip,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.54,0:32:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,it is not important
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.54,0:32:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they were right or wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.54,0:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.96,0:32:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is to fix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.96,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so lovingness then
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.96,0:32:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes a healingness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.96,0:32:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its intention to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.96,0:32:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to heal out of its understandingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.56,0:32:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a different energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.56,0:32:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,than the one called love by the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.56,0:32:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world calls love
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.56,0:32:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of sentimentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.56,0:32:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming out of a solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.56,0:32:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.56,0:32:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we hear somebody say,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.56,0:32:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,well I used to love Joey
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.56,0:32:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't love him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.56,0:32:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What they really mean
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.56,0:32:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is they never loved Joey.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.56,0:33:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What they had was a sentimental attachment,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.56,0:33:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a dependency,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.56,0:33:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a back and forth control,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.56,0:33:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a lustful attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.56,0:33:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,controlling ownership
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.56,0:33:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and an emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.56,0:33:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of their childishness
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.56,0:33:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and a feeling of loss
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.56,0:33:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,if that person leaves their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.56,0:33:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is truly loving
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.56,0:33:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is an inner intention and a commitment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.56,0:33:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so it creates a stable energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.56,0:33:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which never changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.56,0:33:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If I decide to love you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.60,0:33:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,which is my own intention
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.60,0:33:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then there's nothing you can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.60,0:33:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a stable unchanging energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.60,0:33:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.60,0:33:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see it in the non-judgmentalism
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.60,0:33:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.60,0:33:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Or somebody might have come into a group
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say who shot three people last week
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.60,0:33:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and ran over some innocent people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.60,0:33:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and what do they say
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.60,0:33:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when he walks into the group meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.60,0:33:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, Joe we sure are glad to see you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.60,0:33:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure need us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.60,0:33:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure need us.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.60,0:33:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The unconditionality of that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.60,0:33:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because what's being related to now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.60,0:34:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the person's beingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.60,0:34:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's being related to is beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.60,0:34:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of the true self
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.60,0:34:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of what that person really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.60,0:34:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving from the small self
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.60,0:34:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with a small s
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.60,0:34:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the large self
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.60,0:34:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital S.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.60,0:34:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the sustaining, nurturing
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.60,0:34:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,healing energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.60,0:34:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.60,0:34:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's crucial for us to see
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.60,0:34:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that that is the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.60,0:34:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.60,0:34:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of the personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.60,0:34:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.60,0:34:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear in AA the saying
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.60,0:34:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, bring the body
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.60,0:34:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll get it by osmosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.60,0:34:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just bring the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.60,0:34:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Principle is about personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.60,0:34:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that the healing field itself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.60,0:34:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is what nurtures and supports
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.60,0:34:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and brings about the miracle of recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.60,0:34:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the importance then of that alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.60,0:34:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,with that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.60,0:34:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because characteristic of AA
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.60,0:34:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is a feeling of gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.60,0:34:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude which is at about 540
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.60,0:35:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of laughter, of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.60,0:35:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And humor is about 550
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.60,0:35:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to come from
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.60,0:35:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a different way of holding our experience
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.60,0:35:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of self-pity, instead of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.60,0:35:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.60,0:35:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in its expression as resentment
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.60,0:35:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we now hold as humor as that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.60,0:35:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which at the time perhaps was tragic.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.20,0:35:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this willingness then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.20,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to be forgiving, to be understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.20,0:35:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this healing nature of the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.20,0:35:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we move up to joyful states
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.20,0:35:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,characterized here as compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.20,0:35:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That desire to heal through understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.20,0:35:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.20,0:35:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which brings about the healing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.20,0:35:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of transfiguration
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.20,0:35:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in one's consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.20,0:35:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of seeing the perfection of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.20,0:35:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing the oneness of all things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.20,0:35:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the oneness of all life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.20,0:36:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up then to 560
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.30,0:36:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which we don't have written on the board
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.30,0:36:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we have an energy field called ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.30,0:36:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,not the jumping up and down
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.30,0:36:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of emotionalism
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.30,0:36:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but an inner experience of extreme serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.30,0:36:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into states
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.30,0:36:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which generically I call bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.30,0:36:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,These blissful states
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.30,0:36:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and these blissful states
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.30,0:36:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of feelings of expansive well-being
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.30,0:36:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of being at one with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.30,0:36:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of generous lovingness and forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.30,0:36:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of inner extreme pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.30,0:36:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This blissful state is important
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.07,0:36:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in the understanding of the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.07,0:36:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because this experience is the most
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.20,0:36:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,addictive of all human experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.20,0:36:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,addictive in a generic sense
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.20,0:36:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not in the terms of the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.20,0:36:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but that the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.20,0:36:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is possible within oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.20,0:36:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience let us say
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.20,0:37:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.20,0:37:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a person studies a meditative technique
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.20,0:37:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and now suddenly they go into an expansive state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.20,0:37:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite oneness and bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.20,0:37:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a state called samadhi.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.42,0:37:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,From this experience of samadhi
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.42,0:37:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the person now is aware of what is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.42,0:37:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and then comes into the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.42,0:37:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,a desire to return to that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.42,0:37:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The knowingness now of what is possible
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.42,0:37:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,creates the desire to return to that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.42,0:37:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person's life usually changes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.42,0:37:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to a considerable degree
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.42,0:37:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,once that has been experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.42,0:37:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and many people will leave their lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.42,0:37:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and shift to a totally different lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.42,0:37:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,directed towards spiritual purification
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.42,0:37:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the removal of all that has obstructed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.42,0:37:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing of this state.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.42,0:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People who have had near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.52,0:37:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and there are many books on that now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.52,0:38:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,near death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.52,0:38:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,where they are declared dead on the operating table
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.52,0:38:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the movie Revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.52,0:38:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,which is about such a person
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.52,0:38:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,very clinically accurate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.52,0:38:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing of that infinite state
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.52,0:38:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of blissfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.52,0:38:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and subsequent to that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.52,0:38:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the dramatic change in the person's lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.52,0:38:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of that experience now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.52,0:38:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.52,0:38:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a different orientation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.52,0:38:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a different context.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.25,0:38:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The movie Lost Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.25,0:38:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,which has always been one of my favorites
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.25,0:38:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,depicts extremely well the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.25,0:38:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as you remember Ronald Coleman in the original version
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.25,0:38:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when he falls into Shangri-La
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.25,0:38:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a state of unconditional lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.25,0:38:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a state which recalibrates
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.25,0:38:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,around a little over 600
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.25,0:38:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and he experiences this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.73,0:38:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.73,0:38:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and then when he tries to return
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.73,0:38:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to the ordinary world
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.73,0:38:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he returns to a world which
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.73,0:38:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,recalibrates around 200
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.73,0:39:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of successful doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.73,0:39:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting this
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.73,0:39:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he cannot find any satisfaction
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.73,0:39:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.73,0:39:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,compared to what he has experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.73,0:39:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and so there was then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.73,0:39:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to return
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.73,0:39:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to that state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.73,0:39:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.73,0:39:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which in the movie is depicted as a place
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.73,0:39:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but which we know is actually
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.73,0:39:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.73,0:39:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire at any cost
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.73,0:39:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to return to that inner state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.73,0:39:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look then at where
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.79,0:39:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all human experience occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.79,0:39:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.79,0:39:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the body is unable to experience itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.79,0:39:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only experienced in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.79,0:39:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the mind that is experiencing the body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.79,0:39:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mind itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.79,0:39:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is experienced by consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.79,0:39:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise you would not be aware
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.79,0:39:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is going on within mind
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.79,0:39:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and so experience is taking place then
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.79,0:39:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,within an energy field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.79,0:39:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is this inner experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.79,0:39:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.79,0:40:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of a blissful state
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.79,0:40:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to which people become addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.79,0:40:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,who have never taken drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.79,0:40:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,now what happens then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.17,0:40:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in the drug experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.17,0:40:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.17,0:40:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.17,0:40:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,like the sun is always shining
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.17,0:40:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these energy fields here
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.72,0:40:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we could say are like the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.72,0:40:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the clouds block off the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.72,0:40:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.72,0:40:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,which is ever shining
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.72,0:40:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and what a drug does then
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.91,0:40:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is it blocks off our experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.91,0:40:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of these lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.91,0:40:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows us to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.91,0:40:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of a higher energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.91,0:40:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,within us
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.91,0:40:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if we could block off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.97,0:40:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,all these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.97,0:40:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.97,0:40:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up to the level of 560
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.97,0:40:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.97,0:40:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if we could find some way
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.97,0:40:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of blocking off all the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.97,0:40:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,blocking off all these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.97,0:40:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up to 560
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.97,0:40:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what would we experience
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.97,0:40:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we would experience what's left
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.97,0:40:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.97,0:41:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy field of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.97,0:41:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and isn't there such a designer drug
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.97,0:41:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and yes indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.97,0:41:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,there is one
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.97,0:41:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,called ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.97,0:41:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,designed specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.97,0:41:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to block off the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.97,0:41:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of all these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.97,0:41:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,other than 560 or over
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.97,0:41:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and so what's happened then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.52,0:41:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,with the drug experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.52,0:41:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is that pharmacologically
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.52,0:41:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,something has blocked off
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.52,0:41:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this lower energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.52,0:41:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowed us to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.52,0:41:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,something of a higher energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.52,0:41:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,so the person coming home
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.52,0:41:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,full of fears and griefs
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.52,0:41:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and regrets and anxieties
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.52,0:41:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,stops in for two martinis
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.52,0:41:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and now suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.52,0:41:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,they jump all these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.52,0:41:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and they move up to an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.52,0:41:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at about 500
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.52,0:41:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what I call mellow
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.52,0:41:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mellow
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.96,0:41:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mellow is that field
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.96,0:41:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where you sort of love everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.96,0:41:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're willing to forgive everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.96,0:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're generous
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.96,0:41:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,easy going
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.96,0:41:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the kids love you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.96,0:41:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when you're in that state
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.96,0:41:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you bring home toys for the children
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.16,0:42:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and flowers for the wife
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.16,0:42:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the energy state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.57,0:42:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and over
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.57,0:42:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that is sought in the drug experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.57,0:42:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the blocking off of that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is below that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.57,0:42:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and allowing the person to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.57,0:42:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.57,0:42:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,so we said these are
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.67,0:42:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,addicting experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.67,0:42:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.67,0:42:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,once having experienced it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.67,0:42:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,wishes to return
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.67,0:42:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we asked the person
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.67,0:42:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who's ever had an addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.67,0:42:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a person who has an alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.67,0:42:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.67,0:42:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.67,0:42:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are seeking
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.67,0:42:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,look at what is the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.67,0:42:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to which they are habituated
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.67,0:42:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to which they return
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.67,0:42:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,over and over again
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.67,0:42:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the price
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.67,0:42:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.83,0:42:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that as an inner state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.83,0:42:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as an inner state of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.83,0:42:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that in reality
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.83,0:42:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't even care about the drug
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.83,0:42:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug was only
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.83,0:42:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the mechanics
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.83,0:42:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the way of accessing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.83,0:42:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the only way that they knew at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.83,0:42:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain way of experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.83,0:43:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,their being
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.83,0:43:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,their existence
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.83,0:43:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a pleasurable
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.83,0:43:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,highly energized state
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.83,0:43:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is what was sought
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.83,0:43:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and if a drug does not block off
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.83,0:43:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,these lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.83,0:43:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow you to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.83,0:43:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that inner state of blissfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.83,0:43:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,then it is no longer used
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.83,0:43:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is not called an addicting drug
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.83,0:43:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you see many of the psychological explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.83,0:43:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.83,0:43:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,try to present it as though
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.83,0:43:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it is a running away
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.83,0:43:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,from these lower experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.83,0:43:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is running away from fear
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.83,0:43:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the person is running away from depression
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.21,0:43:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,well we have some excellent drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.21,0:43:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that will handle that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.21,0:43:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Thorazine for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.21,0:43:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,will knock out your anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.21,0:43:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple of weeks maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.21,0:43:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't feel nervous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.21,0:43:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,until the 4th of July
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.21,0:43:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet nobody calls me up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.21,0:43:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and asks for refills
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.21,0:43:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the same with antidepressants
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.21,0:43:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,an antidepressant will move you out
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.21,0:43:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.21,0:43:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but nobody calls up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.21,0:43:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and says that their prescription
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.21,0:43:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for the antidepressant
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.21,0:43:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is filled on the toilet
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.21,0:43:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,like they would with Percodan
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.21,0:44:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so the alleviation of the depression then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.21,0:44:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the alleviation of the anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.21,0:44:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.21,0:44:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,or the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.21,0:44:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which is well handled
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.21,0:44:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,pharmacologically by traditional medical drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are not good
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.21,0:44:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not considered
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.21,0:44:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to be addictive substances
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.21,0:44:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,why?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.21,0:44:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because they do not block off
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.21,0:44:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,these energy fuels high enough
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.21,0:44:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to experience this higher state
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.21,0:44:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so now we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.21,0:44:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what the person is addicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.21,0:44:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.21,0:44:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to that energy fuel within
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.21,0:44:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to that state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.21,0:44:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to return to that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.21,0:44:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the price they are willing to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.21,0:44:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.21,0:44:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because what the mind begins to demand
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.21,0:44:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is a return to that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.21,0:44:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what the price
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.21,0:44:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to pay the price
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.21,0:44:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,increases with time
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.21,0:44:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so that in the end
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.21,0:44:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,finally it will ask for the body itself
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.21,0:44:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it will say
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.21,0:44:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if you keep on drinking like that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.21,0:44:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you are going to be dead
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.21,0:44:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,within weeks or months
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.21,0:44:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know what the person does about that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.21,0:44:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they go across the street to the bartender
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.21,0:45:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,their old pal Joe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.21,0:45:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they order a martini
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.21,0:45:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.21,0:45:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,guess what the doctor told me today
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.21,0:45:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point the bartender orders them a drink
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.21,0:45:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for all good times
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.21,0:45:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they kiss the body goodbye
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.21,0:45:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to let all of it go
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.21,0:45:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore we see the price that people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.21,0:45:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are willing to pay
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.21,0:45:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for the so called addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.21,0:45:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to this state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.21,0:45:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it mystifies people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.21,0:45:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,who have not accessed that level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.21,0:45:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in their drug experience
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.40,0:45:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,why are these people willing to sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.40,0:45:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.40,0:45:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they are willing to sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.40,0:45:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.40,0:45:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to return to this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.40,0:45:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that energy fuel we call bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.72,0:45:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,now let's remind ourselves that we see
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.72,0:45:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the same thing going on with people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.72,0:45:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who have never taken a drug
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.72,0:45:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,who by virtue of their destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.82,0:45:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or previous spiritual work whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.82,0:45:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,have fallen into the energy fuels
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.82,0:45:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of these higher experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.04,0:45:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see them do the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.04,0:46:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to give up power and money
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.04,0:46:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and position and titles in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.04,0:46:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to devote all of their time and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.04,0:46:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to the returning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.04,0:46:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to this state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.04,0:46:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore that movie
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.04,0:46:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.04,0:46:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.04,0:46:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,really tells us the whole story of addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.04,0:46:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to sacrifice all of it
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.04,0:46:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for a certain state of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.04,0:46:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as though there is an innate inner
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.04,0:46:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.04,0:46:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is really true
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.04,0:46:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is this false start
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.04,0:46:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience what is true
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.04,0:46:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,false start because it doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.04,0:46:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,so the reason for the giving up of the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.04,0:46:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the giving up of the alcohol and drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.04,0:46:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is not because it's wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.04,0:46:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not because it's wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.04,0:46:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but because it doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.04,0:46:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.04,0:46:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because as you move from here
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.04,0:46:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,up to here what happens is you bring about
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.04,0:46:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,as we all know the progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.04,0:46:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of inner self-respect
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.04,0:46:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the reversities and negativities
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.04,0:47:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of these energy fuels the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.04,0:47:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.04,0:47:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,negative experiences in one's life
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.04,0:47:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of the loss of relationships
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.04,0:47:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of credit cards
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.04,0:47:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of status
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.04,0:47:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of physical health
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.04,0:47:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of the function of the body organs
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.04,0:47:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the progressive downhill course
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.04,0:47:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,brought about by the denial of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.04,0:47:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and what is the denial of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.04,0:47:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that is going on here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.04,0:47:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the denial of the truth as we said
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.04,0:47:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything from this level on down
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.04,0:47:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to putting the power
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.04,0:47:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.04,0:47:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we see what's happened in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.04,0:47:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.04,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the person has given this source
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which these people here accept
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.04,0:47:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of their happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.08,0:47:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of meaning in their life
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.11,0:47:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,have projected it into the outer world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.11,0:47:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and given that power to the drug
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.11,0:47:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they've given the power
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.11,0:47:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to some substance outside of themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.11,0:47:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug in and of itself
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.11,0:47:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has no power at all
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.11,0:47:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to create these higher experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.11,0:48:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tested this out in research
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.11,0:48:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for several years
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.11,0:48:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with literally hundreds of people
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.11,0:48:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the classes we've been giving
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.36,0:48:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for instance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.36,0:48:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,people who are fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.36,0:48:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and right in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.36,0:48:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,handling their addictive problem
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.36,0:48:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we've tested with kinesiology
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.49,0:48:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the proposition
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.49,0:48:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has the power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.49,0:48:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to create this higher experience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.49,0:48:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and universally
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.49,0:48:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,100% of the people go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.49,0:48:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with that proposition
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.49,0:48:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,proving that it is a lie
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.49,0:48:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has no power whatsoever
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.49,0:48:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we present them
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.49,0:48:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,with an opposite concept
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.49,0:48:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have everybody in the class
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.49,0:48:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind its opposite thought
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.49,0:48:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that the drug blocks off
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.49,0:48:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy fields that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.49,0:48:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from that which I am not
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.49,0:48:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow me to experience the joyfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.49,0:48:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which is my real self
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.49,0:48:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and instantly everybody in the class
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.49,0:48:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,goes strong
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.49,0:48:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,indicating that it is the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.49,0:48:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,so the truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.49,0:48:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the drug has no power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.49,0:48:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to create these experiences whatsoever
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.49,0:49:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it has the pharmacologic capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.62,0:49:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to block off these negative energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.62,0:49:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and allow you to at least
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.62,0:49:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,get into the ballpark
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.62,0:49:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't the real state of bliss of course
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.62,0:49:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the person who has earned it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.62,0:49:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,through their own progressive spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.62,0:49:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but at least in the ballpark
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.62,0:49:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of what that experience is like
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.62,0:49:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.62,0:49:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is closest to
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.62,0:49:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of one's own being
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.45,0:49:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,can we utilize
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.45,0:49:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,this knowledge now
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.03,0:49:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in understanding the recovery from addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.03,0:49:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when the person comes in with an addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.38,0:49:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they are usually at the bottom of the box
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.38,0:49:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,full of self-hatred, hopelessness, despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.38,0:49:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,regret, despondency
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.38,0:49:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see that the energy field down here
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.70,0:49:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of apathy, of hopelessness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.70,0:49:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is one in which the person cannot help themself
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.70,0:49:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and hopeless means just that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.70,0:49:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and a friend of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.70,0:49:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who was president of the county bar association
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.70,0:50:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,literally died of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.70,0:50:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,alone in a rooming house
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.70,0:50:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,addicted to a combination of valium and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.70,0:50:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,never even picked up the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.83,0:50:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to call anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.83,0:50:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,literally died of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.83,0:50:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a person of that caliber
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.83,0:50:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,with thousands of friends
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.83,0:50:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,all of whom would have dropped anything
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.83,0:50:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to come and help him
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.83,0:50:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless means just that means that
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.83,0:50:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no point in making the phone call
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.83,0:50:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because there is no hope
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.83,0:50:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that hopelessness about one's condition
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.96,0:50:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which often expresses itself as
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.96,0:50:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my case is different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.96,0:50:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,my case is different
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.96,0:50:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning you may well recover from this
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.96,0:50:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but my case is hopeless
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.96,0:50:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this apathy, this hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.96,0:50:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in which God is dead
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.96,0:50:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what can we do for the person
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.96,0:50:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because the process over here in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.96,0:50:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of loss of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is de-energized
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.96,0:50:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the woman who is rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.96,0:50:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in her rocking chair
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.96,0:50:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,staring out the window blankly
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.96,0:50:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all we can do is pour energy into that person
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.12,0:50:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,reason doesn't have any effect
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.12,0:51:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that when the telegram
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.12,0:51:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,from the state department came
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.12,0:51:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and said it was a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.12,0:51:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that her energy field didn't change
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.12,0:51:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,she kept right on rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.12,0:51:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and staring out the window
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.12,0:51:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so the answer is to pour energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.12,0:51:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,into that person
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.12,0:51:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by our concern
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.12,0:51:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by our lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.12,0:51:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by our physical presence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.12,0:51:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through nutrition
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.12,0:51:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in every possible way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.12,0:51:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we pour energy into that person
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.12,0:51:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and get them up to the next energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.47,0:51:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,called grief
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.47,0:51:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,grief
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.47,0:51:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,grief has to do with the past
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.47,0:51:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and next what the person will experience
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.47,0:51:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when they come out of the shock
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.47,0:51:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they come in a blank shock like state
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.47,0:51:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is they will begin to cry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.47,0:51:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to regret
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.47,0:51:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss that all this addiction has cost them
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.47,0:51:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,regret
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.47,0:51:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling self-pity
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.47,0:51:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sorrow for the fact that they are
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.47,0:51:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in a rehabilitation place
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.47,0:51:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or they are in the space they are in life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.47,0:51:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they are very sad about life
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.47,0:51:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,sad about their addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.56,0:51:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they feel completely neglected by God
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.56,0:51:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and so there is this spirited state
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.56,0:52:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spirit being that willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.56,0:52:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.56,0:52:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of life itself
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.56,0:52:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so this regret about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.56,0:52:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,we move the person's energy field up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.56,0:52:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we move them up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.56,0:52:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.56,0:52:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which is one of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.56,0:52:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,at this point the person begins to fear the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.56,0:52:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,worry and anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.56,0:52:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,fear has to do with the future
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.56,0:52:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,they are no longer in the inflated state of denial
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.56,0:52:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,on the contrary they are deflated
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.56,0:52:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the world looks frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.56,0:52:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they perhaps feel that God is punishing them
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.56,0:52:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for their past sins
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.56,0:52:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so they are misinterpreting the addiction now
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.56,0:52:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as a punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.56,0:52:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they are fearing a punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.56,0:52:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of more punishment
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.56,0:52:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and further loss in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.56,0:52:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but the energy of each thing can move up
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.98,0:52:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to the energy of the next
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.98,0:52:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we move the person out of the fear of the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.98,0:52:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,into the desiring for something better
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.98,0:52:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,desiring something other than being victim
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.98,0:52:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.98,0:52:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the craving this
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.98,0:52:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the wanting to move into something better for yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.98,0:53:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and move them up to anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.98,0:53:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,anger as we said has a lot of useful energy in it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.11,0:53:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not the form of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.11,0:53:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,not the form of anger itself
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.11,0:53:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but the energy of anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.11,0:53:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the person then becomes angry
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.11,0:53:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,over their predicament in life
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.11,0:53:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,angry over being victim
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.59,0:53:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,this anger then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.59,0:53:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that we see it used in society
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.59,0:53:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in a constructive way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.59,0:53:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw the way we see the way minority groups
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.59,0:53:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,get angry over the injustices
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.59,0:53:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of their social position
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.59,0:53:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and use the energy of that anger
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.59,0:53:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to mobilize social forces
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.59,0:53:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and move up to pride
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.59,0:53:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in doing something about it
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.59,0:53:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to take action
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.59,0:53:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to take action
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.59,0:53:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to begin to move up into
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.59,0:53:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.59,0:53:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for one's position
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.59,0:53:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and moving up to the next energy field of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.00,0:53:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,courage is crucial in the addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.00,0:53:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.00,0:53:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we see the powerful effect then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.00,0:53:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the first step has
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.00,0:54:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the admission that we're powerless over alcohol or drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.00,0:54:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now allows us to face
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.00,0:54:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,cope, handle
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.00,0:54:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and be appropriate
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.00,0:54:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we become re-empowered
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.00,0:54:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we now see the world
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.00,0:54:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.00,0:54:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the first time we have an open mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.00,0:54:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,truth has a way
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.00,0:54:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter our mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.00,0:54:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we move the person
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.00,0:54:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we utilize the pride
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.00,0:54:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to move the person up in the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.00,0:54:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look at the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.00,0:54:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and in looking at the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.00,0:54:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraging them to move up to the next position
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.00,0:54:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is letting go, resisting the facts
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.00,0:54:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be released from that resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.00,0:54:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can begin to view the world as an okay place
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.00,0:54:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and begin to utilize and experience their own freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.00,0:54:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom to explore, to expand
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.00,0:54:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and move them up to the willingness then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.36,0:54:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to say yes in this exploration
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.36,0:54:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to join it, to agree, to align with it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.36,0:54:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and they join their intention
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.36,0:54:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so they begin to see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.36,0:54:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole rehabilitative process
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.36,0:55:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world in which it is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.36,0:55:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as friendly
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.36,0:55:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,they begin to see Alcoholics Anonymous, let's say
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.36,0:55:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as promising and hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.36,0:55:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that perhaps they will recover
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.36,0:55:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and move them up into acceptance then
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.36,0:55:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a very powerful energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.36,0:55:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,where you are beginning to see
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.36,0:55:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have the power to make these decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.36,0:55:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the confidence, the feeling of adequacy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.36,0:55:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the transformation that comes about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.36,0:55:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the experiencing that the world is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.36,0:55:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it is on the one hand presented you with a problem
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.36,0:55:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other hand it is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.36,0:55:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in that it also provides you with the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.36,0:55:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is a merciful God provides you with solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.36,0:55:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so although you may have an addiction
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.36,0:55:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you find that there are hundreds of thousands of people around
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.36,0:55:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who have found the answers
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.36,0:55:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,who are only too willing to help you with this
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.36,0:55:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the world begins to look
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.36,0:55:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,friendly, harmonious, merciful, helpful, hopeful
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.36,0:55:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and with acceptance and the letting go of the resistance
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.80,0:55:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the letting go of denial
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.80,0:56:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into an energy field of lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.80,0:56:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,where the person then commits themself
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.80,0:56:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to an energy field which is healing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.80,0:56:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by joining one of the 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.80,0:56:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the person's willingness to align with it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.28,0:56:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,their willingness to accept it
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.28,0:56:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so through that willingness then comes acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.28,0:56:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the acceptance of the truth about this
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.28,0:56:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we need to be in an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.28,0:56:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is nurturing, supportive and understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.28,0:56:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which is unconditionally loving
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.28,0:56:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,move the person into that energy field then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.83,0:56:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and we know that they are in a safe space
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.83,0:56:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain aligned with that then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.83,0:56:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is to ensure one's survival
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.83,0:56:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and with that experience comes the joyfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.96,0:56:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of the experience of an inner serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.96,0:56:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning to see the perfection and the oneness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.96,0:56:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the energy field which you are now part and parcel of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.96,0:56:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was the willingness to tell the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.18,0:57:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,moving us up through this very critical level
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.18,0:57:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the first step, our willingness to admit
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.18,0:57:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that we were powerless over alcohol and drugs
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.18,0:57:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that was making our life unmanageable
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.18,0:57:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the second step then becomes very significant
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.18,0:57:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it says in all of the 12 step groups
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.18,0:57:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the second step was the restoring us to sanity
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.18,0:57:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,by some power greater than ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.18,0:57:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the intuitive understanding of the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.18,0:57:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the small self
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.18,0:57:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will take something with much greater power
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.18,0:57:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,than its smallness to handle this problem
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.18,0:57:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at bliss and we see that the energy field of that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.18,0:57:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,starting at about 500 and running all the way up to 600
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.18,0:57:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a powerful electromagnet pulling one
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.18,0:57:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,back into wanting to re-experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.18,0:57:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that experience in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.18,0:57:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore to handle it something of an equal dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.18,0:57:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of an equal dimension will be needed to handle it
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.18,0:57:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so the second step is really the intuitive knowing of that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.18,0:57:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that something greater than the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.18,0:58:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the limited small self
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.18,0:58:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to be needed to handle the attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.18,0:58:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of such a powerful energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.18,0:58:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the third step then is the decision that comes out of that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.18,0:58:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.18,0:58:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the third step is one of surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.18,0:58:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,turning the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.18,0:58:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to turn one's life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.18,0:58:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,over to God as one understands him
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.18,0:58:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.18,0:58:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just out of willingness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.18,0:58:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you see
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.18,0:58:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that the God of alcoholics
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.18,0:58:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of one's own understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.18,0:58:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is already a friendly, promising and hopeful God
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.18,0:58:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,using the example of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.18,0:58:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that one sees who have done this
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.18,0:58:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning willingness to be trusting
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.18,0:58:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning elements of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.18,0:58:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the third step then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.18,0:58:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the step of deep surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.18,0:58:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,really moves one into this alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.18,0:58:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy field of 500 and over
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.79,0:58:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the rest of the steps now make sense
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.79,0:58:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of course from the viewpoint of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.79,0:59:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as we've looked at it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.79,0:59:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the fourth step says
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.79,0:59:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that we looked within the box
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.79,0:59:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.79,0:59:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what was in the box
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.79,0:59:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own particular case
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.79,0:59:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,took a fearless moral inventory
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.79,0:59:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to look at all that was negative in our life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.79,0:59:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,our willingness to own that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.79,0:59:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and then in the fifth step
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.79,0:59:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a very healing step
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.79,0:59:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,admit to ourself, to God
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.79,0:59:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and to another human being
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.79,0:59:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact nature of that which we discovered within the box
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.79,0:59:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.79,0:59:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we change the energy field of it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.79,0:59:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we take the charge off of it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.79,0:59:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we take the negativity off of it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.79,0:59:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so that now the same event
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.79,0:59:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,although it hasn't changed in history
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.79,0:59:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we are holding it has changed
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.79,0:59:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so that which had the capacity to corrode
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.79,0:59:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroy us before
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.79,0:59:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is now rendered inoperative
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.79,0:59:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,see Bill Wilson used to say
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.79,0:59:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that the correct attitude about the past
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.79,0:59:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is a decent regret
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.79,1:00:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a decent regret
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.79,1:00:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,one may regret it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.79,1:00:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's quite a bit different
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.79,1:00:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,than self-hatred leading to self-destruction
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.79,1:00:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,instead one comes from the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.98,1:00:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill used to say
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.98,1:00:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,AA is the language of the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.98,1:00:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.98,1:00:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with its humor
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.98,1:00:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with its lightness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.98,1:00:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at the past
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.98,1:00:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to heal it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.68,1:00:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the healing then comes out of the step five
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.68,1:00:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it's expressed in steps six through nine
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.68,1:00:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which are really
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.68,1:00:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the reparative steps
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.68,1:00:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those are steps in which
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.68,1:00:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the person takes responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.68,1:00:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to actually do something in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.68,1:00:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to repair any damage that is repairable
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.68,1:00:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to mend whatever fences can be mended
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.68,1:00:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it's not just a mental intellectual exercise
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.68,1:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it becomes real
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.68,1:00:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and relieves all the guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.68,1:00:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,about what one has done in the past
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.68,1:00:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to one's best ability
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.68,1:00:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,one goes back into the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.68,1:00:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to repair
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.68,1:00:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the damages that have been done
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.68,1:01:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the degree that they're repairable
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.68,1:01:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,step ten then
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.29,1:01:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,says that this way of life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.29,1:01:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of taking responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.29,1:01:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for the content of our own consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.29,1:01:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to clean it up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.29,1:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that this became our way of life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.42,1:01:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and we began to do this on a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.42,1:01:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,on a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.42,1:01:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we looked within the box
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.42,1:01:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to see what had gone wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.42,1:01:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what was out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.42,1:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,what was lacking in integrity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.42,1:01:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where could we have done better
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.42,1:01:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where could we have been more loving
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.42,1:01:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so the owning then of the process
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.42,1:01:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual progress
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.42,1:01:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,our commitment to that as a way of life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.42,1:01:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is step ten
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.58,1:01:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,step eleven is interesting then
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.58,1:01:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because it says
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.58,1:01:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what it says is if we do steps one through ten
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.58,1:01:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if we make that our lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.58,1:01:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will reconnect with something
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.58,1:01:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that we sought in the first place
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.58,1:01:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,through drugs and alcohol
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.58,1:01:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it says sought through prayer and meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.58,1:02:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to increase our conscious contact with God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.58,1:02:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we understood
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.58,1:02:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,asking only for his will for us
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.58,1:02:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power to carry it out
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.58,1:02:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,see loving doesn't say
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.58,1:02:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we began
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.58,1:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it said it already happened
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.58,1:02:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it said that when we committed ourselves to loving this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.58,1:02:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as a lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.58,1:02:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we reconnected
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.58,1:02:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we began to reconnect through the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.58,1:02:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which is divine
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.58,1:02:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is God
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.58,1:02:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is love
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.58,1:02:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,are all the same thing are they not
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.58,1:02:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as we committed to loving this
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.58,1:02:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as our style and way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.58,1:02:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to the best of our ability
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.58,1:02:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we began to reconnect with some
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.58,1:02:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,rock like inner experience
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.58,1:02:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,which was similar to that which we sought in the first place
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.22,1:02:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then step twelve gives away
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.22,1:02:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what the whole addictive process is about
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.22,1:02:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,what its whole nature is in the field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.22,1:02:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,step twelve says
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.22,1:02:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,having become conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.22,1:02:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of this total experience
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.22,1:02:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the language of the twelfth step is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.22,1:02:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,having had a spiritual awakening
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.32,1:02:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,having become conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.32,1:03:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,having had a spiritual awakening
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.32,1:03:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of the entire addictive experience
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.32,1:03:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we carried this message to others
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.32,1:03:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and expressed it in our entire life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.32,1:03:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so the twelfth step tells us then
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.32,1:03:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what the whole purpose of the addictive process was
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.32,1:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to awaken us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.32,1:03:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to move us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.32,1:03:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from one level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.32,1:03:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to another
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.32,1:03:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from being asleep and unaware
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.32,1:03:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to being awake and conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.32,1:03:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and aware and responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.32,1:03:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from being unconscious and irresponsible
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.32,1:03:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from being helpless victim
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.32,1:03:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to owning ourselves as the source
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.32,1:03:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and being responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.32,1:03:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,for the happiness within our life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.32,1:03:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop putting it out there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.89,1:03:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to stop saying that the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.89,1:03:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is outside of myself
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.89,1:03:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that the source of my happiness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.89,1:03:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is the same as the source of my life
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.89,1:03:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to own myself irresponsibly
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.89,1:03:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as a spiritually aware person
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.92,1:03:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so now we have a different context
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.92,1:03:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the whole addictive process
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.92,1:04:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a movement of advancing and increasing
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.92,1:04:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.92,1:04:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that alcoholism and drugs then
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.92,1:04:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,require that a person become more awake
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.92,1:04:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to survive
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.92,1:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and here we have a disease that is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.92,1:04:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively fatal
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.92,1:04:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the only way to recover from the illness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.92,1:04:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is to become progressively spiritually aware
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.92,1:04:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively more conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.92,1:04:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so that life itself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.92,1:04:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on becoming conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.92,1:04:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a major self confrontation
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.92,1:04:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,something that our higher self
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.92,1:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has picked for us
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.92,1:04:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that will force us to grow
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.92,1:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no turning back
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.92,1:04:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no reprogramming the brain cells
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.92,1:04:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,once they're programmed
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.92,1:04:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's not enough room on the tightrope
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.92,1:04:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to turn around and change one's mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.92,1:04:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and once one is into the addictive
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.92,1:04:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholic process
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.92,1:04:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no turning back
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only the confront
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.92,1:04:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with owning the truth about oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.92,1:04:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and total recovery depends on
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.92,1:04:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting that process
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.92,1:05:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,moving joyfully into it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.92,1:05:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,being grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.92,1:05:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you hear now
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.92,1:05:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you understand why
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.92,1:05:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you hear speakers at meetings of AA for instance say
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.92,1:05:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're grateful they're an alcoholic
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.92,1:05:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to the newcomer this sounds indeed like madness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.92,1:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,grateful?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.92,1:05:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,how could one be grateful?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.92,1:05:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're coming from self hatred
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.92,1:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and guilt about this thing
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.92,1:05:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how could one be grateful?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.96,1:05:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how could one be grateful
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.96,1:05:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that one has become addicted or an alcoholic
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.96,1:05:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because that forced us to grow
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.96,1:05:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it forced us to become conscious
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.96,1:05:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it forced us to become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.96,1:05:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we become grateful to the process
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.96,1:05:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at first resenting it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.96,1:05:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at first resisting it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.96,1:05:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then actually accepting it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.96,1:05:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then agreeing with it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.96,1:05:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then beginning to love
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.96,1:05:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then experiencing joy
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.96,1:05:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and then achieving that state called serenity
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.96,1:05:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.96,1:05:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was your destiny
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.96,1:05:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this was your way of doing it
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.96,1:05:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the way that you chose
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.96,1:05:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.96,1:05:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's wonderful
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.96,1:06:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's sort of an awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.96,1:06:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that you never could have reached this understanding
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.96,1:06:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,any other way
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.96,1:06:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,some people just have to experience it this way
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.96,1:06:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for those who did
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.96,1:06:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,great gratitude comes about
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.96,1:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and a greater understanding of the nature of consciousness itself
